# CurrencyTracker — code-owner routing.
#
# Each line maps a glob pattern to one or more owners (GitHub handles or
# team slugs). When a PR touches a matching path, the listed owners are
# auto-requested as reviewers. With branch protection's "Require review
# from code owners" on (enabled in 0.29), merge is blocked until at least
# one listed owner approves.
#
# Order matters: the LAST matching line wins. Catch-all `*` goes FIRST,
# then more specific patterns can override it.
#
# Today the maintainer is the sole owner. Per-directory stanzas are kept
# so re-assignment (when a teammate joins) is a one-line edit, not a
# restructure.

# Catch-all: every path defaults to the maintainer.
*                                @mpcs2013

# Application source — Clean Architecture layers (added from Phase 2).
/src/Domain/                     @mpcs2013
/src/Application/                @mpcs2013
/src/Infrastructure/             @mpcs2013
/src/Api/                        @mpcs2013
/src/Worker/                     @mpcs2013
/src/AppHost/                    @mpcs2013

# Tests — kept structurally separate from src/.
/tests/                          @mpcs2013

# Infrastructure as code (added from Phase 14).
/infra/terraform/                @mpcs2013

# CI/CD and repo metadata (added from Phase 0.C onwards).
/.github/                        @mpcs2013

# Documentation, ADRs, runbooks.
/docs/                           @mpcs2013

# Frontend (added in Phase 16).
/web/                            @mpcs2013